"The University at Buffalo (UB) is a public research university located in Buffalo, New York. It was founded in 1846 and is the largest and most comprehensive campus in the State University of New York (SUNY) system. UB offers over 400 undergraduate, graduate, and professional degree programs across 13 schools and colleges, including the Jacobs School of Medicine and Biomedical Sciences, the School of Engineering and Applied Sciences, and the School of Management. The university is known for its strong research programs in areas such as nanotechnology, biotechnology, and social sciences. UB is also home to the Center for the Arts, which hosts a variety of cultural events and performances throughout the year."